quran[15]{c,v,t,f}:
  50,31,"And Paradise will be brought near to the Muttaqûn (the pious. See V.2:2), not far off."
  50,32,"(It will be said): "
  50,33,""
  51,25,"When they came in to him and said: "
  51,26,"Then he turned to his household, and brought out a roasted calf [as the property of Ibrâhîm (Abraham) was mainly cows]."
  51,27,"And placed it before them, (saying): "
  52,16,"Taste you therein its heat and whether you are patient of it or impatient of it, it is all the same. You are only being requited for what you used to do."
  52,17,"Verily, the Muttaqûn (the pious. See V.2:2) will be in Gardens (Paradise), and Delight."
  52,18,"Enjoying in that which their Lord has bestowed on them, and (the fact that) their Lord saved them from the torment of the blazing Fire."
  53,10,"So (Allâh) revealed to His slave [Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم through Jibrîl (Gabriel) عليه السلام] whatever He revealed."
  53,11,"The (Prophet’s) heart lied not in what he (Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم) saw."
  53,12,"Will you then dispute with him (Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم) about what he saw [during the Mi‘râj: (Ascent of the Prophet صلى الله عليه وسلم to the seven heavens)]{1}",footnotes:1:[{53:12} Al-Mi‘râj (i.e. Ascent of Prophet Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم to the heavens with his body and soul (بالروح والجسد).]
  54,1,"The Hour has drawn near, and the moon has been cleft asunder (the people of Makkah requested Prophet Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم to show them a miracle, so he showed them the splitting of the moon).{1}",footnotes:1:[{54:1} Narrated Anas رضي الله عنه: The people of Makkah asked the Prophet صلى الله عليه وسلم to show them a sign (miracle). So he showed them (the miracle) of the cleaving of the moon. (Sahih Al-Bukhari, Vol.6, Hadîth No.390).]
  54,2,"And if they see a sign, they turn away, and say: "
  54,3,"They belied (the Verses of Allâh - this Qur’ân), and followed their own lusts. And every matter will be settled (according to the kind of deeds: good deeds will take their doers to Paradise, and similarly evil deeds will take their doers to Hell)."